   <body>
      <context>
         <p>Before you can release a lock on a document, it must be checked out. Releasing a lock reverts the check-out of the document you are working on <i>without checking it in</i>. You can only release a lock when you have the document open in X-Author.</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>From the X-Author pane, click on the <image placement="inline"
                      width="16"
                      href="../attachments/45220101/49676309.png"
                      id="image_cp1_gkn_12c"/>
               <uicontrol>Lock Status</uicontrol> tab icon.</p>
            <stepresult>
               <p>The Lock Status page shows agreement details and information on the current
                  document lock.</p>
               <fig id="fig_lgl_r4j_12c">
                  <image height="400"
                         placement="break"
                         href="../attachments/45220101/49676310.png"
                         id="image_mgl_r4j_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </stepresult>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Release Lock</uicontrol> on the Lock Status page.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>If you chose to release the lock, the document check-out is reverted. Any changes
               you made while the document was checked out are not saved.</p>
            <stepresult>
               <p> The page refreshes to reflect unlocked status and most menu options are
                  disabled.</p>
               <fig id="fig_px2_m2q_12c">
                  <image height="400"
                         placement="break"
                         href="../attachments/45220101/49676311.png"
                         id="image_rx2_m2q_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </stepresult>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <div>
         <note type="note">
            <p>If you release a document lock in error and want to continue working with the document, go to the Lock Status page and click <uicontrol>Acquire Lock</uicontrol>.</p>
         </note>
      </div>
   </body>
